                  </persName>
            . I am a cutler, and live in Tower-street. On the 20th or 21st of September the prisoner came and asked me to buy some blades; I might have seen him before, but I did not know him - he asked me 2s. for one dozen of blades; he came the next day to know if I would buy the others, and I would not.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you not ask me many times if I had got such things? A. Never in my life.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He has called me out of the gate many times, and asked me, and in the street too; I had no work for fifteen months, and was willing to do any thing I could.</p>
